---
import { getLocale, localizedPath, type Locale } from "../i18n/utils";
import LegalNotice from "./LegalNotice.astro";
const locale: Locale = getLocale(Astro.url.pathname);
const about = localizedPath("/about", locale);
---

<article
  class="container-prose py-12 [&_h2]:mt-8 [&_h2]:text-xl [&_h3]:mt-5 [&_h3]:text-lg [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_li]:text-gray-400 [&_p]:mt-3 [&_p]:text-gray-400 [&_ul]:mt-3 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:space-y-1 [&_ul]:pl-6"
>
  <LegalNotice />
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">Version 1.0.0 · Effective 2026-05-26</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <h3>When you apply</h3>
  <p>
    Application form data: name, email, Telegram handle, OS, RAM, internet
    quality, timezone, English fluency level, programming experience, AI tool
    experience, motivation essay, project idea, weekly time commitment,
    preferences (class format, code-stuck response, team role), and your honest
    answer to "why should we pick you."
  </p>
  <h3>When you participate</h3>
  <p>
    Attendance records, session feedback (anonymous or named), code you post in
    cohort channels, PRs you submit to the Tour Repo (public), and optional demo
    day recordings (with explicit opt-in).
  </p>
  <h3>Automatically</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Site analytics (only if enabled — currently none for Cohort 1)</li>
    <li>
      Server logs from third-party hosts (GitHub Pages, Telegram, etc. — see
      their policies)
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why we collect it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Application data:</strong> to score and select cohort participants per
      the <a href={about}>public scoring rubric</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Attendance:</strong> to ensure the cohort runs and to identify students
      needing support
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>PRs:</strong> to maintain the public cohort archive (your portfolio)
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Demo recordings:</strong> only with your explicit consent at recording
      time
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Selection-scoring CSV:</strong> deleted 12 months after the cohort ends
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Application form raw data:</strong> deleted 12 months after the cohort
      ends
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cohort channel messages:</strong> stay in Telegram per Telegram's retention;
      we don't archive separately
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Tour Repo public PRs:</strong> stay forever (it's a public archive).
      You may request your contributions be anonymized by emailing <a
        href="mailto:ai+privacy@vibecode.tours">ai+privacy@vibecode.tours</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Demo day recordings:</strong> kept indefinitely if posted publicly with
      your consent; deletable on request
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who sees it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Selection data:</strong> lead instructor + named scoring team members
      only (currently: lead instructor only). Never sold. Never shared with third
      parties.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Attendance:</strong> instructor only</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Channel messages:</strong> cohort + instructor (Telegram itself sees
      them per their policy)
    </li>
    <li><strong>PRs + demo recordings:</strong> public, per your consent</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third parties</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>GitHub</strong> (Tour Repo + this site): see <a
        href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
        >GitHub privacy statement</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Telegram</strong> (cohort channel): see <a
        href="https://telegram.org/privacy">telegram.org/privacy</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>YouTube</strong> (unlisted setup video): see <a
        href="https://www.youtube.com/intl/en/howyoutubeworks/our-commitments/protecting-user-data/"
        >YouTube data commitments</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Anthropic</strong> (Claude API): your API usage data is governed by
      Anthropic's terms if you bring your own key; if we provide credits via LiteLLM
      proxy, proxy logs are deleted within 30 days
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Application form provider</strong> (Tally.so or Google Forms): see their
      policies
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>You may at any time:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Request a copy of all data we hold about you</li>
    <li>Request correction of any data</li>
    <li>
      Request deletion of your application data (we will delete and notify you
      of completion within 30 days)
    </li>
    <li>Request anonymization of your contributions to the public archive</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent for any recording</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Contact: <a href="mailto:ai+privacy@vibecode.tours"
      >ai+privacy@vibecode.tours</a
    >
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    We do not accept applicants under 18. If you discover that you provided
    information while under 18, please contact us immediately for deletion.
  </p>

  <h2>International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    This site is hosted by GitHub (US). Application form data may be processed
    by Tally.so (EU) or Google Forms (US). By applying, you consent to these
    transfers.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use HTTPS site-wide. Application form data is stored in the form
    provider's encrypted database. Selection scoring is done on the instructor's
    local machine, never on cloud storage.
  </p>

  <h2>Updates</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy. Material changes will be announced via email to
    current cohort participants and posted to this page.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:ai+privacy@vibecode.tours"
      >ai+privacy@vibecode.tours</a
    >
  </p>

  <hr class="mt-10 border-gray-200" />
  <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500"><strong>Version log</strong></p>
  <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 text-sm text-gray-500">
    <li>1.0.0 (2026-05-26) — Initial version</li>
  </ul>
</article>
